Key Match Events: Bas de Leede hit an unbeaten 30* and took 2 wickets with the ball.
Namibia chased 122 with 5 wickets in hand, winning by 5 wickets with 3 balls remaining.
Post-Match Reflections: Jan Frylinck, Namibia's captain, said, 'Never nice to be on the losing side... With the bat it seemed difficult for both sides. They ran better. We tried our best.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Namibia needed 6 runs off the last 6 balls, and Bas de Leede took 2 wickets in the process.
Vikramjit Singh scored 39 runs for Netherlands, while JJ Smit took 2 wickets.
Jan Frylinck was the MVP for Namibia with 64.01 points, scoring 43 runs and taking 1 wicket.
Bas de Leede was named Player of the Match for Netherlands, taking 2 wickets and scoring 30*.
Others: The match took place at GMHBA Stadium in South Geelong, Victoria, on October 18, 2022, as part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2022-23.
